============================================================

Written to `tools/title-loop/docs/7-9a83c46/feedback.md`. Summary of findings:

**Case 1 — Baked Eggs:** The 2-line join likely falls below the embedding threshold because the cleaner single-line prefix scores higher. When `survivingJoins` is empty, the prefix-protection logic doesn't fire, so the dedup "shorter wins" rule keeps the incomplete title.

**Case 2 — CHLEBEK:** The in-recipe section header "WARZYWA I BOCZEK" qualifies as a structural heading just like the recipe title. Multi-title guard sees ≥2 ALL_CAPS headings and returns both, producing a `+`-joined result instead of just the title.

**Case 3 — Faszerowana papryka:** The Korean romanization "PAPRIKA GYERAN-JJIM" appears on line 2 in ALL_CAPS. The structural (+0.10) + allCaps (+0.08) bonuses overwhelm the positional advantage of the Polish mixed-case title on line 1. Multi-title guard collapses to the single ALL_CAPS candidate.

**Case 4 — SAFFRON WHEAT BUNS:** Two independent problems — (a) the OCR reads "/" but the expected output has ":", so even a perfect join can't match; (b) the top-25 pre-filter may exclude the 9-word join in favor of shorter ALL_CAPS candidates, preventing the continuation logic from running.

**Common themes:** continuation joins are fragile (conditional on threshold survival and candidate pool inclusion); intra-recipe ALL_CAPS section headers are indistinguishable from recipe titles; large ALL_CAPS bonuses override document position on bilingual pages.
